    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aji-de-gallina-style-chicken-stew-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and cut your<strong> brown onion[s]</strong> into quarters, then separate the wedges so you end up with a pile of onion petals</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into large wedges</p><p>Crush your <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife and discard the skins</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aji-de-gallina-style-chicken-stew-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>onion petals</strong>, <strong>chopped pepper</strong> and <strong>peeled garlic</strong></p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until starting to char</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aji-de-gallina-style-chicken-stew-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>red chilli[es] </strong>in half</p><p>Tip: Not a fan of spice? Remove the seeds!</p><p>Add your <strong>walnuts </strong>and 50ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [75ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong>, <strong>Italian hard cheese </strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and a very generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aji-de-gallina-style-chicken-stew-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the veg is starting to char, transfer the <strong>charred</strong> <strong>pepper </strong>to the<strong> food processor</strong> with the <strong>garlic </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>onion petals </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>aji de gallina mix</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aji-de-gallina-style-chicken-stew-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the pan with the remaining onion to a high heat and add your <strong>chicken breast strips </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Cook for 5-6 min on each side or until golden and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Meanwhile, blitz the <strong>aji de gallina mix </strong>until smooth \u2013 this is your <strong>aji de gallina sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aji-de-gallina-style-chicken-stew-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Slice the <strong>remaining red chilli</strong> finely</p><p>Once the chicken is cooked through, add the <strong>aji de gallina-style sauce </strong>to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant and thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>aji de gallina-style chicken stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/aji-de-gallina-style-chicken-stew-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>aji de gallina-style chicken stew </strong>with the <strong>cooked rice </strong>to the side</p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into a small bowl and turn out</p><p>Top with the <strong>chopped parsley</strong> and <strong>sliced red chillies</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
